Two suspected robbers have been arrested by DCI detectives in a botched plan to rob members of the public. The two - Caroline Maina and Keith Njoroge - both aged 25, were arrested along the Southern Bypass towards Kikuyu after the DCI was notified by members of the public. "Following an alert at DCI, detectives swung into action and intercepted the said vehicle with altered registration number KCW 675E along Southern Bypass towards Kikuyu," the directorate said. Both suspects have been  placed in custody as further investigations continue, while the  motor vehicle whose original registration number is KCV 675F has been detained. According to the DCI, the suspects were pretending to be stranded and seeking help before robbing those who came to their rescue. The had further altered the original number plate from KCV to KCW using a tape.